      <h2>Who founded DevCon?</h2>
      <h3><span class="caps">Winston Damarillo</span>, Founder</h3>
      <p class="twitter-handle"><a href="http://twitter.com/YGLWinston" target="_blank">@YGLWinston</a></p>
      <p><%= image_tag "faq/winston.jpg", :alt => "Winston", :class => "profile-pic pull-left" %> A seasoned technopreneur and founder of DevCon, US-based Winston Damarillo has always been an advocate of the ICT sector in the Philippines and a believer of Filipino software engineering talent. In December 2009, with full commitment to collaborative knowledge-sharing, Winston opened the “TechBar” in Cebu IT Park, an in-office technology center that provides a venue for Filipino ingenuity to flow freely through interactive sessions, such as the very first BarCamp in the Philippines and other technology user group meetings. There is also a TechBar in Ortigas, Pasig City located in <a href="http://exist.com" target="_blank">Exist</a> which was launched in 2008 and used almost monthly by tech groups for different IT events. Quarterly, he travels to the country to conduct talks, inspiring students and new software developers.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
